Heo Kang-in.

259
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:09,296
I'm sure they were ordered
to attend the trial by Hong Moo-seob.

260
00:18:09,379 --> 00:18:11,673
As in showing respect to superiors.

261
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:18,555
And the military judge already sentenced
his verdict before he entered this court.

262
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:20,766
What?

263
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,519
The military judge said it openly.

264
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:25,437
To not put in effort, like a year ago.

265
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,440
I'd like to apply
for recusal of the judge.

266
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:29,566
It's no use.

267
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,528
It's not enough to be a reason
for recusal of the judge. And…

268
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,948
as long as Hong Moo-seob
is in that position,

269
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:37,366
it's going to be the same.

270
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:41,120
We should make it inevitable
for the military judge to sentence

271
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:42,996
the right verdict.

272
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:52,256
I hope the results of your training
will come out through this trial.

273
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:10,524
Being in the same court like this

274
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:12,442
brings back memories.

275
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:14,278
I know, right?

276
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:17,656
I lost for you at that time.

277
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:20,617
Even if it was a real battle,
the result would've been the same.

278
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:24,830
Speaking of which, I'd like to tell you
that this was what I thought at that time.

279
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,040
What?

280
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:31,503
I wondered how I'll feel
if I crush you in this court.

281
00:19:36,466 --> 00:19:37,301
Did you?

282
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,220
You go ahead and fight with the law.

283
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:44,057
This time, I'll fight with the truth.

284
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:58,864
Yes.

285
00:19:58,947 --> 00:20:00,532
It's going to begin now.

286
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:01,783
What about you?

287
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:03,702
Yes, it’s going to begin here, too.

288
00:20:04,703 --> 00:20:07,164
Detective Doh, I'll leave it to you.

289
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:10,876
You know that I never let go once I bite,
just like Bae-man, right?

290
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:14,588
It runs in the family,
starting with my older brother.

291
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:23,931
Isn't Hong Kyung-ok here yet?

292
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,515
It's late.

293
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:29,102
She did enter the building,

294
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:31,897
but she went
to the Staff Judge Advocate's office.

295
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:33,690
To the Staff Judge Advocate's office?

296
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:36,693
Why would she go there?
This is the interrogation room.

297
00:20:37,277 --> 00:20:39,363
She said the interrogation room
is suffocating,

298
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:41,615
and she said you should go there.

299
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:50,749
So she's trying to intimidate me
from the start?

300
00:20:55,545 --> 00:20:56,755
Please enjoy.

301
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:02,135
Detective Doh, the interrogation…

302
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:05,430
the conversation can take place here.

303
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:07,683
"Conversation"?

304
00:21:10,435 --> 00:21:13,939
Do you think I'm here to have
a conversation with a crime suspect?

305
00:21:14,648 --> 00:21:15,691
What?

306
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:17,651
Crime suspect?

307
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:19,987
What did you say?

308
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,531
You're looking down on a detective?

309
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:24,825
Fine.

310
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:26,493
The place doesn't matter.

311
00:21:27,577 --> 00:21:28,662
Let's begin

312
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:29,788
the interrogation.

313
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,044
Okay.

314
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:42,134
What do you think you're doing?

315
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:43,635
We need to talk.

316
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:47,514
It won't take long. It won't.

317
00:21:55,355 --> 00:21:57,149
Doh Bae-man's aunt.

318
00:21:57,232 --> 00:22:00,986
I know this is a joint investigation,
but I'm in charge here.

319
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:03,572
Please watch your language.

320
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:07,200
What does me being Bae-man's aunt
have to do with this?

321
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:08,827
I'm Detective Doh Soo-kyung.

322
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:10,829
I called you that on purpose.

323
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:12,497
Doh Bae-man's aunt.

324
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:13,999
So you can really feel it.

325
00:22:14,082 --> 00:22:15,542
Doh Bae-man's aunt..

326
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,712
It'll be better when things
turn out nicely.

327
00:22:18,795 --> 00:22:23,216
If you mess with the Corps Commander,
Prosecutor Doh will be in trouble, too.

328
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:26,303
You threaten people

329
00:22:27,137 --> 00:22:29,931
in a really cringy way.

330
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:32,976
Bae-man and I never go easy on anyone.

331
00:22:34,561 --> 00:22:37,814
You, answer my question correctly.

332
00:22:38,815 --> 00:22:39,649
What…

333
00:22:40,442 --> 00:22:42,527
You even talk down to me now?

334
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:44,696
Staff Judge Advocate Seo Joo-hyuk!

335
00:22:45,363 --> 00:22:48,909
Are you a serviceperson, or a prosecutor?

336
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:52,412
Are you a prosecutor, or a serviceperson?

337
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:55,624
Answer me!

338
00:22:56,124 --> 00:22:59,544
Why should I answer you? Why should I?

339
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:03,173
Everyone I met here are servicepeople,

340
00:23:03,256 --> 00:23:05,300
but you have to be a prosecutor!

341
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:10,180
A military prosecutor who charges crimes
accurately and reveals the truth! Get it?

342
00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:14,851
If you go easy on her because she's
the Commander's sister,

343
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:17,437
I will not forgive you.

344
00:23:24,986 --> 00:23:28,198
The fortune teller said I'll be surrounded
by women this year, and this was it.

345
00:23:28,281 --> 00:23:31,993
The Division Commander, Cha Woo-in,
and that vixen.

346
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:35,455
I'm going crazy.

347
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,669
THE FIRST TRIAL OF CORPS COMMANDER
POWER TRIPPING CASE AT HIS RESIDENCE

348
00:23:40,752 --> 00:23:42,212
I'd like to submit evidence.

349
00:23:42,712 --> 00:23:46,174
This was the smartwatch he was ordered
to wear while working at the residence.

350
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:51,638
Corps Commander Hong Moo-seob

351
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:54,224
made Staff Sergeant Shin Min-chul
wear this smartwatch

352
00:23:54,307 --> 00:23:56,518
and called him dozens of times a day.

353
00:23:56,601 --> 00:23:57,978
Violation of human rights--

354
00:23:58,061 --> 00:23:59,771
It hasn't been verified, Your Honor.

355
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:01,106
Sustained.

356
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:05,360
Military Prosecutor,
please only speak of verifiable facts.

357
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:09,489
Then why did you make
Staff Sergeant Shin wear a smartwatch?

358
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:11,283
Wasn't it to give him orders with it?

359
00:24:11,366 --> 00:24:15,829
He only called him three times a day
for the purpose of giving him orders.

360
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:21,293
Does that mean he made him a smartwatch
just to call him three times a day?

361
00:24:21,793 --> 00:24:22,961
Your Honor.

362
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:26,256
May I answer this question, please?

363
00:24:26,339 --> 00:24:27,549
Of course.

364
00:24:29,926 --> 00:24:30,844
Military Prosecutor.

365
00:24:31,553 --> 00:24:34,681
Are you curious about
why I made my subordinate

366
00:24:34,764 --> 00:24:35,891
wear a smartwatch?

367
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:41,062
It was because…

368
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:44,733
I treasured Staff Sergeant Shin.

369
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:49,946
It was because I treasured
Staff Sergeant Shin.

370
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:52,240
What? Treasure him?

371
00:24:52,741 --> 00:24:55,702
You raised your hand
at a person you treasure so much

372
00:24:56,203 --> 00:25:00,123
at a supermarket, about to hit him,
and threw fruit in his face?

373
00:25:07,547 --> 00:25:09,424
Detective, you're not married yet, right?

374
00:25:09,507 --> 00:25:11,927
Those who insist
on remaining single really are selfish.

375
00:25:12,427 --> 00:25:14,179
They only think about themselves.

376
00:25:14,679 --> 00:25:18,391
This is based on selflessness.

377
00:25:18,475 --> 00:25:23,688
I had to scold him for his mistake,
so he won't repeat it again.

378
00:25:23,772 --> 00:25:26,191
Enough with that logic,
which makes no sense at all.

379
00:25:26,274 --> 00:25:29,361
Why did you make Staff Sergeant Shin
cook for your grown-up son,

380
00:25:29,444 --> 00:25:32,072
wash your underwear,
and clean your room, too?

381
00:25:32,155 --> 00:25:33,782
I can explain that--

382
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:36,701
I'll answer her,
so you stay out of this, Lawyer Park!

383
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:38,036
Yes, Madam Hong.

384
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:43,458
To be frank, I didn't curse at him

385
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:44,709
or hit him!

386
00:25:45,293 --> 00:25:48,838
I only cared for him a bit more
because I treasured him.

387
00:25:48,922 --> 00:25:50,131
Selflessness.

388
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:51,299
Okay?

389
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:53,510
It was pity and sympathy, okay?

390
00:25:58,181 --> 00:26:01,101
He provided a smartwatch
for Staff Sergeant Shin.

391
00:26:01,685 --> 00:26:05,480
As you know, smartwatches
have health screening functions.

392
00:26:05,981 --> 00:26:07,524
Health screening?

393
00:26:08,149 --> 00:26:11,987
He was diagnosed with possible arrhythmia,
due to family history.

394
00:26:12,904 --> 00:26:15,282
It was a gift from the defendant
so he could check…

395
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:17,784
his pulse with it.

396
00:26:20,161 --> 00:26:24,332
Who would give an expensive smartwatch
as a gift for violate human rights?

397
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:32,632
And that smartwatch
also has a location tracking function,

398
00:26:33,216 --> 00:26:36,386
so it was also to prevent desertion
from the place of duty.

399
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:38,930
Desertion from the place of duty?

400
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:42,309
Desertion is a felony for servicepeople.

401
00:26:43,143 --> 00:26:47,063
Because of his duty, Staff Sergeant Shin
has to go leave the residence quite often.

402
00:26:47,814 --> 00:26:49,399
His predecessors

403
00:26:49,482 --> 00:26:52,319
were not fully aware of that
and got punished quite often.

404
00:26:52,402 --> 00:26:55,739
So you're saying it was
to prevent Staff Sergeant Shin

405
00:26:55,822 --> 00:26:58,575
from deserting from the place
of duty by mistake

406
00:26:58,658 --> 00:27:00,535
and being punished, aren't you?

407
00:27:00,618 --> 00:27:01,453
Yes.

408
00:27:01,536 --> 00:27:04,539
The smartwatch was not a tool
for power tripping. It was…

409
00:27:06,082 --> 00:27:09,794
a gift that proves the Corps Commander's
consideration for Shin.

410
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:15,800
The trial's going to have a boring ending.
Isn't it a relief?

411
00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:17,552
Just shut up and listen.

412
00:27:20,055 --> 00:27:21,097
Military Prosecution?

413
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:24,893
I'm sure you do not have any more
questions about the smartwatch.

414
00:27:24,976 --> 00:27:25,810
Yes.

415
00:27:26,519 --> 00:27:27,479
I do.

416
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:34,235
It was to prevent
Staff Sergeant Shin's desertion…

417
00:27:35,362 --> 00:27:36,905
All right, I got it.

418
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:40,200
Let me ask you, Staff Sergeant Shin.

419
00:27:41,659 --> 00:27:43,828
What is your affiliation?

420
00:27:44,329 --> 00:27:47,290
I'm affiliated with the HQ Service
of the 4th Infantry Division.

421
00:27:47,374 --> 00:27:48,583
HQ Service?

422
00:27:49,084 --> 00:27:52,462
-Not the Corps Commander's residence?
-No.

423
00:27:52,545 --> 00:27:55,382
Then were you dispatched
to the Corps Commander's residence?

424
00:27:56,257 --> 00:27:58,134
-No.
-Of course you weren't.

425
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:01,721
It is impossible to be dispatched
to the Corps Commander's residence.

426
00:28:01,805 --> 00:28:04,099
Because the residence soldier system
was abolished.

427
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:08,061
The superiors gave orders
to withdraw all military manpower

428
00:28:08,144 --> 00:28:11,022
working in the residence
and replace them with civilian one.

429
00:28:11,106 --> 00:28:13,108
But even if there was an order,

430
00:28:13,191 --> 00:28:16,361
an old custom
is hard to be changed overnight.

431
00:28:17,362 --> 00:28:20,240
The commanders who treat the soldiers
like their servants

432
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:24,244
changed their titles to
the driver soldiers or operation soldiers,

433
00:28:24,828 --> 00:28:28,289
and used non-commissioned
officers instead of soldiers.

434
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:30,625
Staff Sergeant Shin
was personally selected

435
00:28:30,708 --> 00:28:33,503
by Corps Commander Hong Moo-seob
from the first line troops.

436
00:28:34,129 --> 00:28:37,424
So, Staff Sergeant Shin
is already deserting his place of duty,

437
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:40,927
and what do you mean
by preventing his desertion?

438
00:28:41,428 --> 00:28:45,223
Didn't you just ignore all procedures,
take Staff Sergeant Shin

439
00:28:45,306 --> 00:28:46,933
and use him as your servant?

440
00:28:47,016 --> 00:28:47,851
Prosecution!

441
00:28:48,518 --> 00:28:49,853
Watch your language!

442
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:51,229
Health screening?

443
00:28:51,312 --> 00:28:54,149
Do you know how Staff Sergeant Shin's
hearing is right now?

444
00:28:54,232 --> 00:28:57,444
A commander can't know every detail
about a subordinate's medical records.

445
00:28:57,527 --> 00:28:58,903
Sustained.

446
00:28:58,987 --> 00:29:01,448
Prosecution, what does
Staff Sergeant Shin's hearing

447
00:29:01,531 --> 00:29:04,200
have to do with this case? What?

448
00:29:04,284 --> 00:29:05,910
It is very relevant.

449
00:29:06,494 --> 00:29:08,913
Because he was continuously assaulted
by the defendant

450
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:10,331
and his eardrum got damaged.

451
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:13,668
Assault? The prosecution is
speaking of something without grounds!

452
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:15,712
Here's the evidence of assault.

453
00:29:20,049 --> 00:29:21,301
Look at that!

454
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:23,052
PHOTO EVIDENCE OF ASSAULT
ON STAFF SERGEANT SHIN MIN-CHUL

455
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,098
That's serious.

456
00:29:29,017 --> 00:29:30,935
To prove continuous and serious assault

457
00:29:31,019 --> 00:29:33,480
the defendant committed
to Staff Sergeant Shin,

458
00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:36,024
I'd like to have
Staff Sergeant Shin testify.

459
00:29:45,408 --> 00:29:46,242
Well done.

460
00:29:51,581 --> 00:29:53,458
You're keep saying the word "treasure",

461
00:29:54,167 --> 00:29:56,586
then why did you curse
at someone you treasure?

462
00:29:57,086 --> 00:29:58,546
What? Curse?

463
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:02,383
I never cursed. I never did.

464
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:05,470
My brother is a general,
and I am a general's sister.

465
00:30:05,553 --> 00:30:08,139
Why would I do a vulgar thing like that?

466
00:30:08,223 --> 00:30:09,599
Are you sure you didn't do it?

467
00:30:09,682 --> 00:30:10,975
It's not even in that video.

468
00:30:11,601 --> 00:30:14,562
Stop falsely accusing me
and show me the evidence!

469
00:30:14,646 --> 00:30:16,356
The way your lips are moving…

470
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:20,443
-is clearly cursing.
-I said!

471
00:30:22,445 --> 00:30:23,655
I didn't…

472
00:30:23,738 --> 00:30:24,697
Then…

473
00:30:25,281 --> 00:30:26,825
Let's turn up the volume.

474
00:30:27,575 --> 00:30:31,287
The supermarket installed
an expensive CCTV.

475
00:30:31,371 --> 00:30:33,039
You idiot! Snap out of it?

476
00:30:33,122 --> 00:30:34,582
Have you gone deaf? What?

477
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:36,042
You bastard! Hey!

478
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:37,794
You eat this cheap peace of crap!

479
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:42,340
Why didn't you tell me about this?

480
00:30:43,842 --> 00:30:45,301
Yes!

481
00:30:45,385 --> 00:30:47,887
He just couldn't understand
what I told him,

482
00:30:47,971 --> 00:30:50,139
so I ended up yelling at him!

483
00:30:50,223 --> 00:30:51,766
But it's not that bad!

484
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:55,270
Is there anyone that hasn't cursed once,
even while driving?

485
00:30:55,770 --> 00:30:58,481
Yes, I sometimes curse too while driving.

486
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:01,985
When I'm alone,
and when no one can hear me.

487
00:31:02,485 --> 00:31:04,362
Don't show stupid things like this.

488
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:06,489
What was that called again?
Power tripping?

489
00:31:06,573 --> 00:31:08,908
Bring the evidence that I really did that.

490
00:31:08,992 --> 00:31:10,743
Evidence!

491
00:31:12,787 --> 00:31:15,748
Those who are innocent actually…

492
00:31:16,332 --> 00:31:18,001
never demand to show evidence.

493
00:31:18,084 --> 00:31:21,421
This is the conclusion I got
from my 17-year police career.

494
00:31:21,504 --> 00:31:23,214
I don't care about your conclusion.

495
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:24,465
Since you want evidence,

496
00:31:24,966 --> 00:31:27,260
I'll let you meet a witness
who has evidence.

497
00:31:28,553 --> 00:31:29,888
Investigator!

498
00:31:30,597 --> 00:31:33,474
Please let Mr. Han Sam-soo,
the former driver

499
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:35,393
for the Corps Commander, in here.

500
00:31:40,398 --> 00:31:41,316
Long time no see.

501
00:31:41,816 --> 00:31:42,942
It's me, Sam-soo.

502
00:31:43,651 --> 00:31:47,322
The driver soldier who almost became blind
because of the ashtray you threw at me.

503
00:31:52,493 --> 00:31:54,579
She made me wear
a smartwatch for 24 hours.

504
00:31:56,789 --> 00:31:58,458
I got a call every five minutes,

505
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:01,044
and I was about to go crazy.

506
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:04,380
"Go bring me water.
Cold water. Put ice in it."

507
00:32:04,464 --> 00:32:07,216
My 24 hours always belonged to that woman.

508
00:32:07,717 --> 00:32:12,138
Hey, how dare you tell a lie
and turn me into a criminal!

509
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:14,891
I'm going to sue you for libel!

510
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:17,310
What are you doing, Mr. Park?

511
00:32:17,393 --> 00:32:19,729
Write a complaint
about this bastard right now!

